  "texts": [
    "Hence X ′ ⊆ Y ′, and the other direction is the same, so h b is injective.For part 4, suppose X ∈ F b, so X ∈ P F. Then assuming h is robust, there is anX ′ ∈ P F ′ such that h[X] = h[S F] ∩ X ′.",
    "We claim that h -1 [X ′] = X.",
    "Since h[X] = h[S F] ∩ X ′, we have that h -1 [h[X]] = h -1 [h[S F] ∩ X ′] = h -1 [h[S F]] ∩ h -1 [X ′] = S F ∩ h -1 [X ′] = h -1 [X ′].",
    "Then since h is robust, h -1 [h[X]] = X, which with the previous sentence gives us h -1 [X ′] = X, so h b [X ′] = X.",
    "This shows that h b is surjective.Parts 5-6 are easy to check.Thus, we arrive at the first part of the categorical picture that we prepared for in Remark 3.10.Corollary 5.10 (The (•) b Functor)."
